      <p><p>The main factor driving the bitcoin bubble is not quite speculation, but manipulation and money laundering. This is a currency where anyone with a couple of millions of, let's say drug money, can easily, anonymously, untraceably _and legally_ laundry their money while at the same time making money off minor players.</p><p>If they're ambitious they can even set up their own -still anonymous, still legal- exchange, where they -legally- can freely manipulate the exchange rate. </p><p>The bitcoin pool is filled with sharks. Caveat emptor.<br/></p></p>
    </div>
    
